phrases: Munch munch munch munch.

For a staff trip, we came to the Chief's sister, Nagisa-san's, place, enjoyed the busy first day,
and now it is the morning of the second day.
But actually, since we were all up late last night, it is closer to noon than morning now.
Morning, Misa-chan.
Yeah.
Morning, Usui.
Does he have low blood pressure?
What are you doing, Misa-chan?
I am waking myself up!
Do not let it bother you!

Sure.

You do not like getting tanned, right?
Right.
If you win the beach volleyball tournament like a man, then my brother will probably accept you more.
Nagisa-san!
Thank you, Nagisa-san!

Huh?
What are you talking about?

I know I can win if I partner up with last year's champion.
Wow.
So Nagisa-san won that?
Why?!
Starting this year, they added an age limit!
So you go find your own partner!
There is no way I can do that.
I do not have any friends here.
You are saying it is impossible?
So you can give up that easily?
In that case, I will have you work here like a man the entire summer.
I am not giving up!
It is not easy at all.
I have been like this my whole life.
No matter if people think I am crazy or I am sick...

This is what makes me the most comfortable!
I will go find a partner.
You have got a man's heart, you know.
Aoi-chan.
But I cannot find a girl who can play beach volleyball that well.
Hey, perfect timing.
Since I have come all the way here, I want to do some beach sport,
so could you help me learn one?
Misa-chan, you are entering the beach volleyball tournament?
I want you to win and become the Beach Princess.
Good luck!
Beach Princess?
You did not know?
No.

There will be lots of photo shoots going on for the main event.

I see.
I am not very interested in that,

I will go for the win.
Excuse me, I need to go practice with Aoi-chan.
What?
Your partner is Aoi-chan?
Misa-chan.
What, Usui?

No.

I am sure.

Confident?
No, more like my fighting spirit is up.
I am not that confident about it.
It is just my desire to win.
It is Aoi-chan's eyes.
Seeing eyes like that inspires me to cheer them on.
Of course, I have never done it, so I do not know if I will be any good.

Do not go, Ayuzawa.

Sorry to make you wait.
God, you are late.
Are you open?

The sand under the foot!
The gusting wind!

Absolute victory!

Misakichi?

Erika-san?!

Now you have said it!
Fine!
Bring it on, damn it!
Take this!
Winner: Ayuzawa-Hyoudou.
Yeaaah!

Do not lose to the sand!
Not so fast!

Those two...

Not bad.
He is so cool!

I am sure there is several schemes going on here.
Usui!
No going easy on us, you hear?!
What is wrong with him?

Who do you think will be this year's Princess?
I hope it is that sexy girl.
Look, she is with her boyfriend.
I am hoping it is the other girl.

No, he would not do that.

I mean, when I really need it, he always helps out.
The final match, begin!
Go!
The first set is won by the Usui-Erika pair!
They are pretty good.
It was stupid of me to think like that.

He has total control over the ball.
He is also incredibly experienced.
Starting the second set!
Damn it, what is wrong with him?
He is not tired at all.
And here we are, running around the court.
Yeah, since he keeps on aiming at nasty places.
But I will not give up.
Aoi-chan.
I will get to it!

Aoi-chan!
Nice control.
Damn it.

He is always annoying,

You make me think you are a decent guy...
You are making me so frustrated.
Why is Usui trying to be my enemy?!
What?
What did I just say?
Well are not you selfish, Misa-chan?
You do not want me as your enemy?
You want me?
You moron!
I did not say anything like that!
Really?
Then are you ready?
Where are you popping it to?!
He is never going to get it.

Hit it!
Aoi-chan!
Nope.
That is not going to make it.
I will get it no matter what!
Misa-chan!
All right!
Watch out!

All good.

You need first aid.
They made a big deal out of it.
Usui!
Do not move around a lot yet.

But...
It is my fault, so of course I would worry!

You can count on me!
Hey!
Do not outshine me!
What?
I want to be the Princess, too.
Aoi.
I definitely saw your determination.
Congratulations.
Nagisa-san.
You know, you are really reckless, Misa-chan.
You plowed through them.
Usui, I am sorry.
I am not forgiving you.
What would you do if I said that?

Aoi-chan was so-

I did not want you to become the Beach Princess, wear clothes that guys like,

That is why?
What is wrong?

Yeah.

Get what?

I am not joking right now.

Fireworks?

Yes, I know.

Sure.

Us too.

Misa-chan!
Come back!

Bye bye.

Here, eat this.
Wow!
